WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:09.040 --> 00:00:14.800
To start, I had hoped to work in this quote from&nbsp;
Isaac Asimov. “There is a cult of ignorance in&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:00:14.800 --> 00:00:20.080
the United States, and there has always been.&nbsp;
The strain of anti-intellectualism has been a&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:00:20.080 --> 00:00:25.080
constant thread winding its way through our&nbsp;
political and cultural life, nurtured by&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:00:25.080 --> 00:00:29.960
the false notion that democracy means that ‘my&nbsp;
ignorance is just as good as your knowledge.’”&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:00:30.960 --> 00:00:36.320
This quote is from 1980, and it’s been echoed&nbsp;
by other great thinkers like Carl Sagan,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:00:36.320 --> 00:00:40.880
who spoke about the public being unable to&nbsp;
grasp the technology we all use every day,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:00:40.880 --> 00:00:45.560
and having no ability to set their own agenda&nbsp;
or ask the right questions, culminating in a&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:00:45.560 --> 00:00:53.120
celebration of ignorance. He said that in 1995.&nbsp;
Even these two could not have foreseen how bad&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:00:53.120 --> 00:00:58.160
this has gotten in the 21st century, with people&nbsp;
now questioning the shape of the Earth and the&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:00:58.160 --> 00:01:04.400
validity of basic arithmetic. This anti-science&nbsp;
fervor makes us easy to manipulate, because any&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:01:04.400 --> 00:01:10.200
contrarian message is bought en masse, no matter&nbsp;
who is telling it or what their motives are. We&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:01:10.200 --> 00:01:16.560
are witnessing a multimodal anti-science empire&nbsp;
operating through mass media and legislation,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:01:16.560 --> 00:01:21.720
moving towards state-sanctioned pseudoscience.
And we don’t have to speculate as to how&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:01:21.720 --> 00:01:26.600
harmful this can be. We have history to&nbsp;
reflect upon. Persecution of scientists&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:01:26.600 --> 00:01:31.760
under Stalin was widespread. Lysenko was&nbsp;
a non-scientist who was promoted to a high&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:01:31.760 --> 00:01:36.280
scientific position under Stalin’s regime,&nbsp;
and who convinced Stalin that genetics and&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:01:36.280 --> 00:01:42.280
relativity were evil. He denied the existence&nbsp;
of genes. To address agricultural problems,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:01:42.280 --> 00:01:48.080
he promoted a pseudoscientific practice called&nbsp;
vernalization, and millions died of starvation as&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:01:48.080 --> 00:01:54.240
a result of crop failures. Scientists who refused&nbsp;
to renounce genetics were left destitute or even&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:01:54.240 --> 00:02:01.680
executed. Are we at risk of repeating such events?&nbsp;
Absolutely. Let’s face reality, Trump is going to&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:02:01.680 --> 00:02:07.080
win the election. Could he bring a Lysenko-like&nbsp;
figure into his cabinet and begin persecuting&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:02:07.080 --> 00:02:12.760
real scientists? Absolutely. Will he try to&nbsp;
expand executive power and abuse his position&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:02:12.760 --> 00:02:18.120
to the point of authoritarianism? Probably. And&nbsp;
there are plenty of wealthy people who will help&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:02:18.120 --> 00:02:24.440
him try to do that. I won’t go into detail about&nbsp;
Project 2025, but it’s not a conspiracy. It’s a&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:02:24.440 --> 00:02:30.160
real plan to move America into the first stages of&nbsp;
Christian theocracy, and it’s already under way.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:02:30.160 --> 00:02:35.160
This is the evil upon our doorstep, and while it&nbsp;
should receive far more attention than people like&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:02:35.160 --> 00:02:40.320
Terrence Howard, we should recognize that it’s&nbsp;
all different shades of the same phenomenon.&nbsp;

00:02:40.320 --> 00:02:44.960
Anti-science sentiment does not arise out of&nbsp;
thin air. Science is becoming increasingly&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:02:44.960 --> 00:02:49.680
more complicated and therefore difficult for&nbsp;
the public to understand, and some people lash&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:02:49.680 --> 00:02:55.120
out due to the discomfort this produces. But&nbsp;
more importantly, there are vested interests in&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:02:55.120 --> 00:03:01.440
promoting this mentality stemming from Republican&nbsp;
funded think tanks, the deliberate sculpting of a&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:03:01.440 --> 00:03:07.640
populace that is not only science illiterate but&nbsp;
actively hostile toward science. Denial of climate&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:03:07.640 --> 00:03:12.600
change is in the interest of energy producers.&nbsp;
Denial of basic evolutionary biology is in the&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:03:12.600 --> 00:03:17.400
interest of Christian theocrats. These efforts&nbsp;
go all the way up the ladder to figures like&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:03:17.400 --> 00:03:22.840
the Koch brothers. I’m not saying Terry is funded&nbsp;
by the Koch brothers, but he rides this prevalent&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:03:22.840 --> 00:03:28.840
attitude of reality denial and hostility toward&nbsp;
any form of expertise to this bizarre prominence&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:03:28.840 --> 00:03:34.200
that now has people questioning 2nd grade math.
To wield an agenda that is in opposition with&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:03:34.200 --> 00:03:39.840
science, one must popularize the notion that&nbsp;
science is wrong and evil. Universities,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:03:39.840 --> 00:03:45.280
the places where you gain knowledge, are evil.&nbsp;
Don’t go there and learn things so that you&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:03:45.280 --> 00:03:50.480
figure out how to resist our brainwashing, and&nbsp;
also how to organize and topple our political&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:03:50.480 --> 00:03:55.480
structures. Universities are famously places&nbsp;
that stand up against the powers that be,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:03:55.480 --> 00:04:00.800
so they must be demonized. It is a successful&nbsp;
campaign because many people are happy to&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:04:00.800 --> 00:04:05.800
have a reason to not learn anything and cling to&nbsp;
primitive beliefs without basis or self-scrutiny.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:04:05.800 --> 00:04:10.800
It goes without saying that religion is a&nbsp;
primary driver of anti-science mentality&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:04:10.800 --> 00:04:16.040
because scientific progress, particularly as of&nbsp;
late, has challenged many religious narratives,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:04:16.040 --> 00:04:21.400
such as immaculate divine creation. This triggers&nbsp;
fear of mortality, as their narrative is eroded,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:04:21.400 --> 00:04:25.360
and they lash out in precisely the same&nbsp;
way as one would defend themselves against&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:04:25.360 --> 00:04:31.280
physical violence, with hostility and tribalism.
At the same time this is not purely a religious&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:04:31.280 --> 00:04:36.000
issue, it has at this point completely&nbsp;
permeated secular politics. I myself am&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:04:36.000 --> 00:04:40.840
not a Democrat and I no longer vote Democrat&nbsp;
out of total disillusionment with the party,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:04:40.840 --> 00:04:45.560
as it does not have the best interests of the&nbsp;
American people in mind. But the Republican&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:04:45.560 --> 00:04:53.320
party is cartoonishly apocalyptic in comparison.&nbsp;
Know-nothing, proudly stupid, in denial of truly&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:04:53.320 --> 00:04:59.160
all science, actively pushing us back into&nbsp;
the dark ages in terms of both ignorance and&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:04:59.160 --> 00:05:04.640
authoritarian control by the church. In the wake&nbsp;
of this, to pretend that idiots like Terry should&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:05:04.640 --> 00:05:10.440
be given a voice is preposterous. He is not the&nbsp;
culprit but he exacerbates larger trends already&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:05:10.440 --> 00:05:16.120
in place. He does not deserve a platform. He is&nbsp;
not part of any legitimate conversation. And most&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:05:16.120 --> 00:05:21.240
of the figures with any kind of expertise that&nbsp;
shoe-horn their way into the conversation have&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:05:21.240 --> 00:05:27.200
ulterior motives as well, and only serve&nbsp;
to further confuse the public. Like Eric.&nbsp;

00:05:27.200 --> 00:05:32.560
So let’s get down to brass tacks. What&nbsp;
is anti-intellectualism at its core?&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:05:32.560 --> 00:05:39.600
It boils down to three principles. 1) Religious&nbsp;
anti-rationalism. Essentially emotions over facts.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:05:39.600 --> 00:05:46.920
2) Populist anti-elitism, or the rejection of&nbsp;
intellectual institutions. And 3) Instrumentalism,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:05:46.920 --> 00:05:51.920
the belief that pursuit of knowledge only&nbsp;
serves practical means, namely profit. This&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:05:51.920 --> 00:05:57.000
movement intends to halt the acquisition of new&nbsp;
knowledge that would undermine groups with power&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:05:57.000 --> 00:06:01.880
and privilege. Misinformation that benefits&nbsp;
those in power is perpetuated, and those&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:06:01.880 --> 00:06:07.000
who speak truth to that power are preemptively&nbsp;
character assassinated. The educational sphere&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:06:07.000 --> 00:06:12.160
is not completely blameless, admittedly. Part of&nbsp;
the disdain towards academia is fostered by the&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:06:12.160 --> 00:06:17.760
increasingly high cost of education. But this is&nbsp;
not in itself a justification for abandoning the&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:06:17.760 --> 00:06:23.280
sanctity of centers of knowledge. Corporations&nbsp;
do not have their financial interests challenged&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:06:23.280 --> 00:06:27.400
when the public can not even identify&nbsp;
the issues that they are harmed by,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:06:27.400 --> 00:06:32.840
thus perpetuating their own subjugation. We can&nbsp;
historically blame the fossil fuel industry,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:06:32.840 --> 00:06:38.720
the tobacco industry, and so forth, but we do&nbsp;
not extend this to scientific knowledge itself.&nbsp;

00:06:38.720 --> 00:06:43.760
Politicians, corporations, and religious&nbsp;
institutions stand to benefit the most from&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:06:43.760 --> 00:06:49.360
promoting anti-intellectualism. They enact the&nbsp;
politicization of non-partisan issues, polarizing&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:06:49.360 --> 00:06:55.600
things like climate change so severely that simply&nbsp;
acknowledging basic science gets one ostracized.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:06:55.600 --> 00:07:01.480
This spills over into the social realm just as&nbsp;
easily. Anti-intellectualism breeds nationalism,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:07:01.480 --> 00:07:06.760
or the same blind allegiance to a governing body&nbsp;
that is actively sowing the seeds of division.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:07:06.760 --> 00:07:11.760
This is the reason for equating Black Lives&nbsp;
Matter or any other kind of social justice with&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:07:11.760 --> 00:07:17.720
“fascism”, and the justification for this always&nbsp;
involves inventing violent intent out of thin air.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:07:17.720 --> 00:07:23.160
This in turn is used to justify a militarized&nbsp;
police force under the guise of protection.&nbsp;

00:07:23.160 --> 00:07:28.760
And lastly, anti-intellectualism promotes&nbsp;
being skeptical towards perceived authority&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:07:28.760 --> 00:07:34.240
while demanding that people blindly follow&nbsp;
demagogues who are amplified by social media.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:07:34.240 --> 00:07:39.040
People who fall into this way of thinking will&nbsp;
place an unreasonable level of skepticism on&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:07:39.040 --> 00:07:44.440
the body of knowledge produced by tens of&nbsp;
thousands of scientists operating all over&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:07:44.440 --> 00:07:49.440
the world under every type of government&nbsp;
and in both the public and private sector,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:07:49.440 --> 00:07:55.080
yet they place absolutely zero scrutiny on the&nbsp;
figures who confidently feed them the narratives&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:07:55.080 --> 00:08:00.960
they enjoy, which are riddled with distortion and&nbsp;
fabrication almost without exception. These people&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:08:00.960 --> 00:08:06.000
find comfort in the strength and confidence&nbsp;
such figures convey in an appeal to shared&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:08:06.000 --> 00:08:11.360
beliefs. That’s why Trump famously stated that he&nbsp;
could shoot someone in the middle of fifth avenue&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:08:11.360 --> 00:08:17.240
and he wouldn’t lose any voters. Because their&nbsp;
idolization of him is emotional, not logical.&nbsp;

00:08:17.240 --> 00:08:24.320
In the end, and here comes Dave the broken record,&nbsp;
anti-science mentality and reality denial is the&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:08:24.320 --> 00:08:29.720
single greatest threat facing mankind.&nbsp;
Take a movie like “Don’t Look Up”. Though&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:08:29.720 --> 00:08:34.920
obviously satirical, the manner in which the&nbsp;
general public in this modern era would react to&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:08:34.920 --> 00:08:42.400
any existential threat was depicted magnificently.&nbsp;
There is no issue that could be more non-partisan&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:08:42.400 --> 00:08:53.801
than a comet coming to kill us all. And yet,&nbsp;
the comet was hyperpoliticized, people were&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:08:53.801 --> 00:08:55.840
brainwashed into believing the comet didn’t exist,&nbsp;
and a megalomaniacal tech oligarch fucked us all.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:08:55.840 --> 00:09:01.520
In my estimation that is roughly what would happen&nbsp;
if there were another far deadlier pandemic or&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:09:01.520 --> 00:09:07.680
some other such situation. And the culprit is&nbsp;
not the scientific community. It’s the pundits&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:09:07.680 --> 00:09:14.240
and demagogues who abuse the power of the internet&nbsp;
to warp public perception of reality. People like&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:09:14.240 --> 00:09:19.360
Rogan are not the main culprits but they also&nbsp;
are not blameless, and deserve their share of&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:09:19.360 --> 00:09:26.080
criticism for amplifying the chaos for monetary&nbsp;
gain. And sadly, other than directly neutralizing&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:09:26.080 --> 00:09:31.560
sources of disinformation and promoting general&nbsp;
science literacy, I don’t have a meaningful&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:09:31.560 --> 00:09:37.600
solution to this doomsday recipe. I don’t know&nbsp;
how to fundamentally change human nature to&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:09:37.600 --> 00:09:43.360
be either less corrupt and manipulative,&nbsp;
or less blindly credulous. I will admit,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:09:43.360 --> 00:09:49.760
my youthful optimism has been diminished as I&nbsp;
enter middle age. But I’m not giving up just yet.

